# Project Conventions

- TypeScript strict mode, never use `any` — use `unknown` with type guards instead
- Functional components only, always use named exports
- File naming: PascalCase for component files, camelCase for hooks/utils
- 3D components go in `src/components/three/`
- UI components go in `src/components/ui/`
- Hooks in `src/hooks/`, lib utilities in `src/lib/`
- Use `@/*` path alias for all imports (maps to `./src/*`)
- Client components must have `"use client"` directive at the top
- All constants and config belong in `src/lib/` — no magic numbers in components
